# ============================================================
# WORLD CORE RUNTIME
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: runtime
domain: world
scope: world.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for world.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers world-aware visibility,
world selection or resolution,
cross-world boundary enforcement,
historical world display,
and bounded failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible world state must distinguish:
- current active world
- restricted world
- historical world
- archived world

## validation_rules
- world identity must resolve
- requested scope must belong to the declared world
- cross-world access must be valid
- historical/reference mode must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid world identity
- invalid cross-world scope
- invalid historical reference
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish world resolution,
scope validation,
cross-world denial,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- world-aware runtime is explicit
- cross-world validation is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
